
[1]defendant

   DEFENDANT, a.

   1. Defensive; proper for defense.

   2. Making defense; being in the character of a defendant.

                                DEFENDANT, n.

   1. He that defends against an assailant, or against the approach of
   evil or danger.

   2. In law, the party that opposes a complaint, demand or charge; he
   that is summoned into court, and defends, denies or opposes the demand
   or charge, and maintains his own right. It is applied to any party of
   whom a demand is made in court, whether the party denies and defends,
   or admits the claim and suffers a default.
